The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Indians held

 Kathmandu, Feb. 21 (PTI): Four Indians have been arrested for illegally carrying weapons in Kapilvastu district of Nepal bordering India.

 They were arrested for possessing illegal arms, Nepal police said. A handmade gun, one round of bullets and two iron rods were recovered from them, they added. A police patrol arrested the men in the border area where the incidents of looting are on the rise. 




